  <!-- Slide 2: What is DCC? -->
  <div class="slide" id="what-is-dcc">
    <h2>What is DCC?</h2>
    <p>DCC (Dynamic Currency Conversion) allows international guests to see and pay the amount in their home currency.</p>
    <i class="fas fa-exchange-alt icon"></i>
  </div>

  <!-- Slide 3: Overseas Payments & Charges -->
  <div class="slide">
    <h2>Overseas Payments & Charges</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Stamp duty</li>
      <li>International payment fee</li>
      <li>Cross-border charges</li>
      <li>Exchange rate fluctuations (varies by bank and country)</li>
    </ul>
    <i class="fas fa-coins icon"></i>
  </div>

  <!-- Slide 4: Exchange Rate Calculation -->
  <div class="slide">
    <h2>Exchange Rate Calculation</h2>
    <p>Customers usually check Google exchange rates before making a purchase. Reality: Final bank statements often differ due to extra charges and rate variations.</p>
    <i class="fas fa-calculator icon"></i>
  </div>

  <!-- Slide 5: How DCC Works -->
  <div class="slide">
    <h2>How DCC Works</h2>
    <p>DCC Rate Calculation: Reuters rate + 6.99% markup. The amount paid and the bank statement amount remain the same, avoiding surprises.</p>
    <p><strong>Key Benefit:</strong> Predictable exchange rate at the time of purchase.</p>
    <i class="fas fa-chart-line icon"></i>
  </div>

  <!-- Slide 6: Benefits for Your Resort -->
  <div class="slide">
    <h2>Benefits for Your Resort</h2>
    <p><strong>MDR (Merchant Discount Rate) Comparison:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Standard card transactions: Resort receives only USD 97 (assuming 3% MDR on a USD 100 transaction).</li>
      <li>With DCC: The full USD 100 is received by the resort with no deductions.</li>
    </ul>
    <i class="fas fa-hand-holding-usd icon"></i>
  </div>

  <!-- Slide 7: Guest Experience & Compliance -->
  <div class="slide">
    <h2>Guest Experience & Compliance</h2>
    <p>DCC is Optional: Guests must not be forced into DCC.</p>
    <p><strong>Best Practice:</strong> Display both home and local currency options at checkout.</p>
    <p><strong>41 Currencies Available:</strong> Provide a seamless experience for global travelers.</p>
    <i class="fas fa-users icon"></i>
  </div>

  <!-- Slide 8: Conclusion & Call to Action -->
  <div class="slide">
    <h2>Conclusion & Call to Action</h2>
